				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Mearis wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">There are a few Zek mages that post on those boards rather intelligently, so hopefully there won't be a stream of 'who cares about PvP in EQ etch'.
<br />

<br />
I mainly wanted to post about how GoD will affect PvP.  Right now, I am sure most mages can sympathise, our nukes are so pathetic in PvP versus people with high end gear because of the way resists were revamped.
<br />

<br />
I recently did a parse of high end resists with a bard friend of mine, and here is some scary data.
<br />

<br />
Using a 26% fire focus, and a 15% spell haste item, chain casting Sun Vortex as fast as I could against a target who was NOT moving, I sustained a wopping ... 56 DPS, over 50 casts on someone with 500 sv vs all.  This is about half the damage of a high end bard melee'ing, and this was against a target who made no attempt to interrupt me or move OOR.
<br />

<br />
While the PoP pets were somewhat of an upgrade to the Epic pet (and this mainly due to Epic Procs not landing) Epic is still by far our best PvP pet, unless we are fighting people with resists so low that the Earth Pet root lands after Mala.  The main reason Epic is our best pet, is because its PROC dps is not PvP nerfed and lands reasonably well on people with high resists, and the MAIN reason is that EPIC pet has at least some sort of MR and innate run speed.
<br />

<br />
The main number one issue that plagues our pet, is how 'easy' to ROOT and SNARE they are.  Protection of Calliav is a great weapon against idiots, but any wizard worth anything with just flux staff pet 3 times then root it.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, the main thing that I wanted to ask for were small changes that would NOT affect PvE mages much, but would be direly needed for PvP mages.
<br />

<br />
- Give a -100 resist modifier to Burning Sands.  The spell in its current form sucks so much and is not worth using at all.  This would give mages a nuke worth using in PvP.  I do not think this would come near stepping on wizard toes as lures are a totally different matter, and -100 is a drop in the ocean (I am at 280 FR unbuffed, and I a not even in the elementals yet)
<br />

<br />
- Make protection of Calliav work on SPELL HITS only, do not make it wear off from someone 'meleeing' the pet two or three times.
<br />

<br />
- Most of all, make monster summoning IV have innate run speed and HIGH mr.  What is my definition of high?  Think EPIC in Velious, the pet should be very hard to root without debuffs, currently with new PoP roots our pets get rooted out of fights insanely fast.
<br />

<br />
I realize most of those changes do not affect many of you, but I think those are 'fairly' innocuos changes that are direly needed.
<br />

<br />
EDIT:
<br />
I realize this is not the PvP board, but this is mainly about how GoD spells should help mages, however, if a mod wants to move it, forgive the screw up.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
