				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree as well it is not a PvP change, which is why I am not advocating 'sweeping' changes that I would like to see but I realize would take a lot of manpower to implement and would carry negative consequences to the 'bigger' picture PvE game.
<br />

<br />
Higher Innate MR for pet - Contrary to what people think, pet resists are based on owner resists only for PvE purposes, giving pets their masters resists would be overpowered as much as I would like it.  Perhaps giving pets their masters resists / 1.5 or so?
<br />

<br />
Higher Innate run speed for pets - Again something that makes no difference for PvE, but is a huge boon PvP wise.  In PvE there is no situation where you need a HASTED pet and have no time to buff it with velocity, or when a pet with velocity is not fast enough.
<br />

<br />
Protection of Calliav - Maybe when ganking level 52 lowbies with an EPIC pet people won't melee your pet, but melees I fight can destroy my pet in under 30 seconds while shrugging off your nukes.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
