			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Our PVP pet damage in the end game is pitiful. Against EP or better geared melees, the mitigated and avoided damage after the 66% damage nerf happens is rediculously low. Hell, our pets die on DSes even against hybrids and casters before the casters are in any jeopardy.
<br />

<br />
The earth pet was fine for a few months is fine until you start hitting people with 300+MR who are basically unrootable even with the -30 MR check.
<br />

<br />
Our pets are also FAR too easily removed from combat with snare or root as they have NO MR. Whoever above said that pets use the owners resists is MISTAKEN when it comes to PVP. For PVP pets use their innate resists. If they used the owners resists, I'd be thrilled.
<br />

<br />
My biggest gripe that I have right now is that we have desperate need of some semi-lure based damage forms. Whether that's pet procs or some nuke in our hands, something needs to be done. Alternatively, we need something with double the irresistable debuff capabilities of mala to have any impact on level 65s with 200+ AAs (which is the world we now play in).
<br />

<br />
Our nukes are a joke against anyone with any decent resists (which eveyone on PVP servers has post-VT or EPs).
<br />

<br />
As far as the impact of GOD on mage pvp, basically it's about 3 things:
<br />

<br />
The new pet: how good is its MR, how good is its damage output, how effective are those procs/nukes (which with no resist modifier would seem to indicate "poor"). What effect do the flurry and crit AAs have PVPwise (I'm guessing not enough given how useless our pets are these days)?
<br />

<br />
Second, improved innate run speed. Everyone will have it. You need it too, but at faster speeds it becomes slightly easier to avoid incoming melee damage and makes it harder to have a melee stick on you even when you're debuffed.
<br />

<br />
Third, improved channeling through stuns/kicks/bashes. Critical skill for me.<br />_________________<br /><span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">Sage Svenuce Summonstuff</span></span>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Vallon Zek
<br />
Officer of <a href="http://www.zephyrosguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zephyros</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
