				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have Epic, and love it for PVP yes, but you guys are looking right past Child of Ro.  That pet is a monster in PVP.  If you have 50% haste, just cast him and let him nuke till OOM or dead, then pop out another, don't bother to burnout the pet and go some more.
<br />

<br />
Epic pet no longer runs at his innate high run speed after DPoC focus.  But he does enrage, gains 1 level, 300 hp, +2 melee and proc damage, and regens 270/tic versus 40/tic.  It's a tradeoff.
<br />

<br />
In my opinion, PVP resists should get a nerf just like PVP nukes did.  If I can't land anything, there is no contest to begin with.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eandori (Retired)</a>
